\caption{Architecture of \gym{}. An LLM/VLM agent interacts with the gymnasium through multi-turn observations and actions. The environment is organized in three layers: 10 clinical domains, 187+ specialized tools across six categories, and a knowledge base of 828K medical passages. A 5-dimensional reward function evaluates each completed episode across accuracy, process quality, safety, format, and coherence.}
\label{fig:architecture}
\end{figure}

The environment exposes a standard Gymnasium interface:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Observation space:} Text (up to 100K characters) containing conversation history, tool results, and patient information.
    \item \textbf{Action space:} Text (up to 10K characters) representing either a JSON tool call (\eg{}, \texttt{\{"name": "search\_pubmed", "arguments": \{...\}\}}) or a natural language response.
    \item \textbf{Reward:} A scalar computed from 5 dimensions at episode termination.
\end{itemize}

